:title("TypeScript interpreter") ;
:description("Parses TypeScript and executes it directly, without generating code.

TypeScript is JavaScript plus a static type layer that is erased at run time, so this is
the JavaScript interpreter (see js-interpreter.abnf) widened to accept - and then throw
away - the type syntax. Type annotations on variables, parameters and return values
(': Type'), generic parameter lists ('<T>') on functions, 'as Type' casts (identity),
non-null assertions ('!') and optional markers ('?') are all parsed and dropped. An
'interface Name {...}' and a 'type Name = ...;' are pure type declarations and compile
to nothing. An 'enum' of bare names becomes an object of integer constants
(Color.Red === 0), so member access reads the values back. Everything runtime is exactly
JavaScript: variables are NOT type pinned and need NOT be declared before assignment.

It has: var/let/const (all block scoped), function declarations and anonymous function
expressions with real closures and an 'arguments' array, arrow functions, if/else,
while, do-while, for(;;), for-of, for-in (over an object's own keys), switch (===
comparison, fallthrough, stacked labels, default), classes (fields with initializers, a
constructor, instance and static methods, 'this', 'new', single inheritance with
super(...) and super.method(), with access modifiers and type annotations erased),
break, continue, return, throw (terminates, there is no try/catch), numbers
(doubles, hex 0x literals included), strings with the methods length/charAt/charCodeAt/
indexOf/replace/slice/substring/split/toUpperCase/toLowerCase/trim, template literals,
booleans, null, undefined, arrays (push/pop/shift/unshift/slice/indexOf/join/concat),
object literals, member access (.name and [expr]), method calls, assignment
(= += -= *= /= %=) as an expression (the target may reach through calls: obj[name] = v),
prefix and postfix ++/--, the ternary operator, || and && (short circuit, returning the
operand), == != === !== < > <= >= + - * / % | ^ & << >> >>> and unary - ! ~ typeof.

Deliberately not in the runnable subset (accepted structurally, then reported as
not-implemented under -warn-unsupported): prototypes, try/catch, destructuring,
decorators, namespaces. The type syntax is erased, never executed, so an invalid type
never affects the result.

Every tag composes a small JS closure (a 'thunk') out of the thunks of its children.
Expression thunks return the value, statement thunks return undefined or a signal object
(return/break/continue) that the enclosing statements route.

The program must define main(); the exit code of the metacompiler run is what main()
returns, so the test programs are self checking: they return 0 on success.
The same language is compiled to LLVM IR by typescript-to-llvm-ir.abnf.") ;


// --- main rules

// Shared token productions (languages/lib).
:include("lib/cstyle-comments.abnf") ;
:include("lib/ident-dollar.abnf") ;
:include("lib/dq-strings.abnf") ;
:include("lib/numbers.abnf") ;
:include("lib/bools.abnf") ;

:startRule(Program) ;
:whitespace(Whitespace) ;

// The merged pushes of all top level statements become one program thunk on the global stack.
Program     <~~ pushg(makeSeq(takeAll())) ~~>
            = { Statement } ;

// Every statement production pushes exactly one thunk: function() -> undefined | signal.
// The TypeScript-only declarations (interface / type alias / enum) come first, before
// VarDecl, so 'const enum' is not misread as a 'const' variable named 'enum'.
Statement   = Block | ImportDecl | ExportDecl | NamespaceDecl | DecoratedDecl | Interface | TypeAlias | EnumDecl | ClassDecl | TryStmt | Destructure
            | GenFuncDecl | AsyncFuncDecl | VarDecl | If | While | Do | ForOf | For | Switch | Return | Break | Continue
            | Throw | FuncDecl | DebuggerStmt | Empty | ExprStmt ;

// --- TypeScript module system (import / export) and namespaces. ---
// import binds no runtime values here (the interpreter has no module loader), so every
// import form is accepted structurally and reported as not-implemented. export in front
// of a real declaration is a transparent prefix: the inner class/function/var/type is
// interpreted genuinely (the 'export' is erased); the value-less export forms (export {..},
// export * from, export =, export default <expr>) are accepted and not-implemented.
ImportDecl  <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("import statement", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwImport ( ImportEquals | ImportBare | ImportTypeOnly | ImportFull ) ;
ImportBare  = StringLit [ ";" ] ;
ImportEquals = Id "=" Id "(" StringLit ")" [ ";" ] ;
ImportTypeOnly = KwType ImportClause KwFrom StringLit [ ";" ] ;
ImportFull  = ImportClause KwFrom StringLit [ ";" ] ;
ImportClause = ImportDefault [ "," ( ImportNS | ImportNamed ) ] | ImportNS | ImportNamed ;
ImportDefault = Id ;
ImportNS    = "*" KwAs Id ;
ImportNamed = "{" [ ImportSpec { "," ImportSpec } [ "," ] ] "}" ;
ImportSpec  = [ KwType ] ( Id | StringLit ) [ KwAs Id ] ;

// export: a declaration keeps running (the keyword is dropped); the value-less forms
// notImpl. ExportBody delegates to the ordinary declaration productions, whose thunk
// lands directly on the enclosing frame (ExportDecl adds no frame of its own).
ExportDecl  = KwExport [ KwDefault ] ExportBody ;
ExportBody  = ClassDecl | GenFuncDecl | AsyncFuncDecl | FuncDecl | VarDecl | EnumDecl | Interface | TypeAlias
            | ExportStar | ExportClause | ExportAssign | ExportDefaultExpr ;
ExportStar  <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("re-export (export *)", up.pos)) ~~>
            = "*" [ KwAs Id ] KwFrom StringLit [ ";" ] ;
ExportClause <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("export clause", up.pos)) ~~>
            = "{" [ ExportSpec { "," ExportSpec } [ "," ] ] "}" [ KwFrom StringLit ] [ ";" ] ;
ExportSpec  = [ KwType ] ( Id | StringLit ) [ KwAs ( Id | StringLit ) ] ;
ExportAssign <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("export assignment (export =)", up.pos)) ~~>
            = "=" AssignExpr [ ";" ] ;
ExportDefaultExpr <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("export default expression", up.pos)) ~~>
            = AssignExpr [ ";" ] ;

// namespace / module / declare - the whole ambient/namespace body is skipped.
NamespaceDecl <~~ takeAll(); push(notImplStmt("namespace / module declaration", up.pos)) ~~>
            = [ KwDeclare ] ( KwNamespace | KwModule | KwGlobal ) [ NamespaceName ] SkipBlock ;
NamespaceName = Id { "." Id } | StringLit ;

// A decorator (@Component, @Injectable(...)) is parsed and its effect not implemented;
// the decorated class/declaration itself is still interpreted (its thunk is repushed).
DecoratedDecl <~~ notImpl("decorator", up.pos); push(pop()) ~~>
            = Decorator { Decorator } ( ExportDecl | ClassDecl ) ;
Decorator   = "@" Id { "." Id } [ SkipParen ] ;

// async / generator function declarations are accepted structurally but not implemented
// (there is no event loop / iterator protocol); their bodies are skipped.
AsyncFuncDecl <~~ push(notImplStmt("async function", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwAsync KwFunction [ "*" ] Id [ TypeParams ] SkipParen [ TypeAnnot ] SkipBlock ;
GenFuncDecl <~~ push(notImplStmt("generator function", up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwFunction "*" Id [ TypeParams ] SkipParen [ TypeAnnot ] SkipBlock ;

DebuggerStmt <~~ push(function() {}) ~~>
            = KwDebugger [ ";" ] ;

// --- TypeScript type-only declarations. ---
// An interface and a type alias exist only in the type layer; they are erased to a
// no-op statement (parsed for their syntax, they contribute nothing at run time).
Interface   <~~ push(function() {}) ~~>
            = KwInterface Id [ TypeParams ] [ KwExtends TypeList ] SkipBlock ;
TypeAlias   <~~ push(function() {}) ~~>
            = KwType Id [ TypeParams ] "=" Type [ ";" ] ;

// An enum of bare names becomes an object binding: enum Color { Red, Green, Blue }
// declares Color = {Red:0, Green:1, Blue:2}. Explicit integer values are honored and
// the auto-increment continues from the last value. Both engines compute the same
// {name: value} pairs at parse time, so the interpreter and the compiler agree.
EnumDecl    <~~ push(makeEnum(takeAll())) ~~>
            = [ "const" KwEnd ] KwEnum Id <~~ push({enumName: up.in}) ~~>
              "{" [ EnumMember { "," EnumMember } [ "," ] ] "}" [ ";" ] ;
EnumMember  <~~ push(makeEnumMember(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Id <~~ push({mname: up.in}) ~~> [ "=" EnumVal ] ;
EnumVal     <~~ push({val: parseInt(up.in)}) ~~>
            = ( "0" | "1"..."9" ) :whitespace() { "0"..."9" } :whitespace(Whitespace) ;

// The JS switch: === comparison, fallthrough until break, stacked labels, default
// anywhere. The body is a flat list - the labels must be tried before Statement,
// because 'case 1:' would otherwise parse as two expression statements (semicolons
// are optional).
Switch      <~~ push(makeSwitch(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwSwitch "(" Expression ")" "{" { CaseLabel | DefaultLabel | Statement } "}" ;
CaseLabel   <~~ push({casev: pop()}) ~~>
            = KwCase AssignExpr ":" ;
DefaultLabel <~~ push({isdflt: true}) ~~>
            = KwDefault ":" ;

Block       <~~ push(makeBlockStmt(takeAll())) ~~>
            = "{" { Statement } "}" ;

// var, let and const all declare a block scoped variable in the current scope.
VarDecl     = VarDeclCore [ ";" ] ;
VarDeclCore <~~ push(makeSeq(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwVar Declarator { "," Declarator } ;
// The optional ': Type' annotation is parsed and erased (pushes nothing).
Declarator  <~~ push(makeDecl(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ TypeAnnot ] [ "=" AssignExpr ] ;

// [condThunk, thenThunk] or [condThunk, thenThunk, elseThunk].
If          <~~ push(makeIf(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwIf "(" Expression ")" Statement [ KwElse Statement ] ;

While       <~~ push(makeWhile(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = KwWhile "(" Expression ")" Statement ;

Do          <~~ push(makeDo(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = KwDo Statement KwWhile "(" Expression ")" [ ";" ] ;

// The three optional parts are wrapped with a kind marker, otherwise e.g.
// 'for (;c;)' and 'for (i=0;;)' could not be told apart on the stack.
For         <~~ push(makeFor(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwFor "(" [ ForInit ] ";" [ ForCond ] ";" [ ForPost ] ")" Statement ;
ForInit     <~~ push({k:"init", t:pop()}) ~~> = ForVar | ForExpr ;
ForVar      = VarDeclCore ;
ForExpr     <~~ push(exprToStmt(pop())) ~~> = Expression ;
ForCond     <~~ push({k:"cond", t:pop()}) ~~> = Expression ;
ForPost     <~~ push({k:"post", t:exprToStmt(pop())}) ~~> = Expression ;

// [] or [exprThunk].
Return      <~~ push(makeReturn(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwReturn [ Expression ] [ ";" ] ;

Break       <~~ push(makeBreak()) ~~>
            = KwBreak [ ";" ] ;

Continue    <~~ push(makeContinue()) ~~>
            = KwContinue [ ";" ] ;

Throw       <~~ push(makeThrow(pop())) ~~>
            = KwThrow Expression [ ";" ] ;

// A function declaration binds the closure in the current scope when it executes.
// The generic parameter list '<T>', the parameter type annotations and the return
// type are all parsed and erased; only the parameter names survive.
FuncDecl    <~~ push(makeFuncDecl(pop(), pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = KwFunction Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ TypeParams ] ParamList [ TypeAnnot ] Block ;

ParamList   <~~ push(takeAll()) /* Collect the parameter names into one array. */ ~~>
            = "(" [ TSParam { "," TSParam } [ "," ] ] ")" ;
// A parameter: a plain name, a rest parameter (...xs, bound to the first rest argument),
// or a destructuring pattern (not implemented, bound to a hidden placeholder name). The
// optional '?' marker, ': Type' annotation and '= default' initializer are erased; only
// the name reaches the closure machinery.
TSParam     = { Decorator } ( RestParam | DestructParam | NormalParam ) ;
NormalParam = Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ "?" ] [ TypeAnnot ] [ ParamDefault ] ;
RestParam   = "..." Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ "?" ] [ TypeAnnot ] ;
DestructParam <~~ notImpl("destructuring parameter", up.pos); push("0destructured") ~~>
            = DPattern [ "?" ] [ TypeAnnot ] [ ParamDefault ] ;
ParamDefault <~~ pop() ~~> = "=" AssignExpr ;

Empty       <~~ push(function() {}) ~~>
            = ";" ;

ExprStmt    <~~ push(exprToStmt(pop())) ~~>
            = Expression [ ";" ] ;

// Every expression production pushes exactly one thunk: function() -> value.
Expression  = AssignExpr ;

// Assignment is an expression and associates to the right: a = b = c.
// If the assignment shape does not fit (e.g. 'a == b'), the parser falls back to CondExpr.
AssignExpr  = Assignment | CondExpr ;
Assignment  <~~ push(makeAssign(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Target ( "+=" | "-=" | "*=" | "/=" | "%=" | "<<=" | ">>>=" | ">>=" | "&=" | "^=" | "|=" | "=" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> AssignExpr ;

// An assignable place: a variable, or a member path that may reach through calls
// but must end in a member: findScope(name)[name] = value.
// The local stack holds [name, suffix marker, suffix marker, ...].
Target      <~~ push(makeTargetRef(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> { CallSuffix | DotSuffix | IndexSuffix } ;

CondExpr    <~~ push(makeCond(takeAll())) ~~>
            = NullishExpr [ "?" AssignExpr ":" AssignExpr ] ;

// The nullish coalescing operator (a ?? b) sits just above ||. It is accepted but not
// implemented; the left operand is kept so the expression still yields a value.
NullishExpr <~~ push(makeNiFold(takeAll(), up.pos, "nullish coalescing (??)")) ~~>
            = OrExpr { "??" OrExpr } ;

OrExpr      <~~ push(makeOr(takeAll())) ~~>
            = AndExpr { "||" AndExpr } ;

AndExpr     <~~ push(makeAnd(takeAll())) ~~>
            = BitOrExpr { "&&" BitOrExpr } ;

// The bitwise levels sit between && and equality, like in JS. A single "|" that
// actually starts a "||" fails its right side, the iteration rolls back, and the
// enclosing || level picks it up.
BitOrExpr   <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = BitXorExpr { "|" <~~ push("|") ~~> BitXorExpr } ;
BitXorExpr  <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = BitAndExpr { "^" <~~ push("^") ~~> BitAndExpr } ;
BitAndExpr  <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = EqExpr { "&" <~~ push("&") ~~> EqExpr } ;

// The longer operators must be tried before their prefixes ("===" before "==").
EqExpr      <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = RelExpr { ( "===" | "!==" | "==" | "!=" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> RelExpr } ;

RelExpr     <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = InstExpr { ( "<=" | ">=" | "<" | ">" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> InstExpr } ;

// instanceof and in are relational operators; neither is implemented (the left operand
// is kept as the value).
InstExpr    <~~ push(makeNiFold(takeAll(), up.pos, "instanceof / in operator")) ~~>
            = ShiftExpr { ( KwInstanceof | KwIn ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ShiftExpr } ;

ShiftExpr   <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = AddExpr { ( "<<" | ">>>" | ">>" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> AddExpr } ;

AddExpr     <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = MulExpr { ( "+" | "-" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> MulExpr } ;

MulExpr     <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = ExpExpr { ( "*" | "/" | "%" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ExpExpr } ;

// Exponentiation (a ** b) binds tighter than * / %. It is accepted but not implemented;
// the left operand is kept as the value.
ExpExpr     <~~ push(makeNiFold(takeAll(), up.pos, "exponentiation (**)")) ~~>
            = UnaryExpr { "**" UnaryExpr } ;

UnaryExpr   = PreIncDec | Neg | Not | BitNot | Typeof | Await | Delete | Void | Yield | PostfixExpr ;
// await / delete / void are accepted but not implemented; the operand is still evaluated.
Await       <~~ push(makeNiUnary(pop(), up.pos, "await")) ~~>
            = KwAwait UnaryExpr ;
Delete      <~~ push(makeNiUnary(pop(), up.pos, "delete")) ~~>
            = KwDelete UnaryExpr ;
Void        <~~ push(makeNiUnary(pop(), up.pos, "void")) ~~>
            = KwVoid UnaryExpr ;
// yield / yield* only occur in generators, which are not implemented; the result is undefined.
Yield       <~~ push(makeYield(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwYield [ "*" ] [ AssignExpr ] ;
// Prefix ++/--: the expression value is the new one.
PreIncDec   <~~ push(makePreIncDec(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = ( "++" | "--" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> Target ;
Neg         <~~ push(makeNeg(pop())) ~~>
            = "-" UnaryExpr ;
Not         <~~ push(makeNot(pop())) ~~>
            = "!" UnaryExpr ;
BitNot      <~~ push(makeBitNot(pop())) ~~>
            = "~" UnaryExpr ;
Typeof      <~~ push(makeTypeof(pop())) ~~>
            = KwTypeof UnaryExpr ;

// The postfix forms: i++ evaluates to the old value.
PostfixExpr = IncDec | SuperCall | CallMember ;
IncDec      <~~ push(makeIncDec(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Target ( "++" | "--" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ;

// super(args) delegates to the parent constructor; super.m(args) invokes the parent's
// method on 'this'. popName pulls the optional '.m' out, leaving the argument thunks.
SuperCall   <~~ push(makeSuperCall(popName(), takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwSuper [ "." Id <~~ push({mname: up.in}) ~~> ] "(" [ Arg { "," Arg } [ "," ] ] ")" ;

// A primary expression followed by any mix of calls and member accesses: a.b[i](x).c().
// A call after a member access is a method call: the object becomes 'this' of the callee
// (that is what makes items.slice(1) or str.charCodeAt(0) work on the native values).
// The 'as Type' cast and the postfix non-null '!' are type-layer only: they push
// nothing and so are transparent to foldCallMember (identity at run time). The '!'
// carries a negative lookahead so it is never stolen from the '!=' / '!==' operators.
CallMember  <~~ push(foldCallMember(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Primary { CallSuffix | DotSuffix | IndexSuffix | OptDot | OptIndex | OptCall | NonNullSuffix | AsCast } ;
CallSuffix  <~~ push({kind:"call", args: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = "(" [ Arg { "," Arg } [ "," ] ] ")" ;
// A call argument, allowing the spread form f(...xs). Spread is accepted but not
// implemented; the spread operand is passed as a single argument.
Arg         = Spread | AssignExpr ;
Spread      <~~ notImpl("spread / rest argument (...)", up.pos); push(pop()) ~~>
            = "..." AssignExpr ;
DotSuffix   = "." Id <~~ push({kind:"member", key: makeConst(up.in)}) ~~> ;
IndexSuffix <~~ push({kind:"member", key: pop()}) ~~>
            = "[" Expression "]" ;
// Optional chaining (a?.b, a?.[i], a?.(x)) is accepted but not implemented; it is treated
// as an ordinary member/index/call, so a null/undefined receiver still throws.
OptDot      <~~ notImpl("optional chaining (?.)", up.pos); push({kind:"member", key: makeConst(pop())}) ~~>
            = "?." Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ;
OptIndex    <~~ notImpl("optional chaining (?.[])", up.pos); push({kind:"member", key: pop()}) ~~>
            = "?." "[" Expression "]" ;
OptCall     <~~ notImpl("optional call (?.())", up.pos); push({kind:"call", args: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = "?." "(" [ Arg { "," Arg } [ "," ] ] ")" ;
NonNullSuffix = "!" !"=" ;
AsCast      = KwAs Type ;

Primary     = AsyncArrow | ArrowFn | NewExpr | RegexLit | "(" Expression ")" | FunctionExpr | TemplateLit | ObjectLit | ArrayLit | StringLit | NumberLit
            | True | False | Null | Undefined | VarRef ;

// An async arrow function (async x => x, async () => {...}) is accepted but not
// implemented; async function expressions are handled by FunctionExpr's KwAsync prefix.
AsyncArrow  <~~ push(makeNiArrow(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwAsync ArrowParams "=>" ArrowBody ;

// new C(args) | new C<T>(args): build an instance of the class named C. The generic
// type arguments are erased. Member/call suffixes may follow (new C().m()).
NewExpr     <~~ push(makeNew(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwNew Id <~~ push({cls: up.in}) ~~> [ TypeArgs ] [ "(" [ Arg { "," Arg } [ "," ] ] ")" ] ;

// The optional name of a function expression is accepted but not bound; generics and
// the return type are erased.
FunctionExpr <~~ push(makeFunctionExpr(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = [ KwAsync ] KwFunction [ "*" ] [ Id ] [ TypeParams ] ParamList [ TypeAnnot ] Block ;

// A trailing comma before the closing brace/bracket is allowed (idiomatic TypeScript).
// Members: an object method or spread (both not implemented) are tried before the
// key:value pair and the shorthand form ({x} === {x: x}).
ObjectLit   <~~ push(makeObject(takeAll())) ~~>
            = "{" [ ObjMember { "," ObjMember } [ "," ] ] "}" ;
ObjMember   = ObjSpread | ObjMethod | PropDef | ShorthandProp ;
PropDef     <~~ push(makeProp(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = PropKey ":" AssignExpr ;
// A computed key ({[expr]: v}) pushes the key thunk; makeProp already accepts a thunk key.
PropKey     = Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> | StringLit | ComputedKey ;
ComputedKey = "[" AssignExpr "]" ;
// Shorthand: { x } binds the property x to the variable x.
ShorthandProp <~~ push(makeProp(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = Id <~~ push(up.in); push(makeVarRef(up.in)) ~~> ;
// An object method ({ m() {..} }) and object spread ({ ...o }) are not implemented; the
// member contributes nothing to the object.
ObjMethod   <~~ notImpl("object method", up.pos); takeAll() ~~>
            = [ "get" KwEnd | "set" KwEnd | "async" KwEnd | "*" ] PropKey ParamList [ TypeAnnot ] Block ;
ObjSpread   <~~ notImpl("object spread (...)", up.pos); takeAll() ~~>
            = "..." AssignExpr ;

ArrayLit    <~~ push(makeArray(takeAll())) ~~>
            = "[" [ ArrElem { "," ArrElem } [ "," ] ] "]" ;
ArrElem     = Spread | AssignExpr ;

// Arrow functions: x => x+1, (a, b) => a+b, () => { ... }. They reuse the same
// closure machinery as function expressions; an expression body is an implicit
// 'return <expr>'. Tried before "(" Expression ")" and VarRef so the (params) and
// single-Id forms win; a non-arrow "(" or bare Id fails the "=>" and backtracks.
ArrowFn     <~~ push(makeArrow(takeAll())) ~~>
            = ArrowParams "=>" ArrowBody ;
// The parenthesized form may carry typed parameters and a return type; the single-Id
// form is untyped. Both push only the parameter names.
ArrowParams <~~ push({aparams: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = "(" [ TSParam { "," TSParam } ] ")" [ TypeAnnot ]
            | Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ;
ArrowBody   = ArrowBlock | ArrowExpr ;
ArrowBlock  <~~ push({body: pop()}) ~~>  = Block ;
ArrowExpr   <~~ push({ebody: pop()}) ~~> = AssignExpr ;

// Template literals: `text ${expr} more`. Each ${...} is evaluated and coerced to
// string (JS +); the result is always a string. Whitespace is disabled inside the
// backticks (scannerless), and re-enabled inside a ${...} so the expression may have
// spaces. A lone '$' not starting a "${" is a literal character.
TemplateLit <~~ push(makeTemplate(takeAll())) ~~>
            = "`" :whitespace() { TplExpr | TplChars | TplDollar } "`" :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
TplExpr     <~~ push({expr: pop()}) ~~>
            = "${" :whitespace(Whitespace) Expression "}" ;
TplChars    <~~ push({str: unescapeJs(up.in)}) ~~>
            = TplChar { TplChar } ;
TplChar     = TplEsc | TplPlain ;
TplEsc      = "\\" "\x00"..."\U0010ffff" ;
TplPlain    = "\x00"..."\x23" | "\x25"..."\x5b" | "\x5d"..."\x5f" | "\x61"..."\U0010ffff" ;
TplDollar   <~~ push({str: "$"}) ~~>
            = "$" ;

// for-of over an array or string iterates its elements/characters (genuine).
// for-in is not implemented (it needs host key enumeration, an off-limits extern);
// it is accepted and, under -warn-unsupported, its iterable is evaluated and the
// body skipped. The loop variable may be preceded by var/let/const or be bare.
ForOf       <~~ push(makeForOf(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwFor "(" [ KwVar ] Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~>
              ( KwOf | KwIn ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> Expression ")" Statement ;

// A destructuring binding (var [a, b] = xs / var {x, y} = o) is accepted but not
// lowered; the initializer still runs so its calls stay visible under -warn.
Destructure <~~ push(makeDestructure(pop(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwVar DPattern "=" AssignExpr [ ";" ] ;
DPattern    = "[" [ DElem { "," DElem } ] "]" | "{" [ DField { "," DField } ] "}" ;
DElem       = Id | DPattern ;
DField      = Id [ ":" DElem ] ;

// try/catch/finally is accepted but not implemented (there is no exception model:
// throw already terminates). Under -warn-unsupported the try block runs; catch and
// finally blocks are parsed and dropped.
TryStmt     <~~ push(makeTry(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwTry Block [ KwCatch [ "(" Id ")" ] Block ] [ KwFinally Block ] ;

// A class declaration: fields, a constructor and instance/static methods, executed
// directly. An instance is a plain object carrying a __class descriptor; the descriptor
// holds the methods and the constructor. A method call on an instance dispatches through
// mcall (which follows __super for inheritance); super.m() calls the parent's method on
// 'this'. Access modifiers and every type annotation are parsed and erased.
ClassDecl   <~~ push(makeClassStmt(takeAll())) ~~>
            = [ "abstract" KwEnd ] KwClass Id <~~ push({cname: up.in}); curClassName = up.in ~~> [ TypeParams ]
              [ KwExtends Id <~~ push({ext: up.in}) ~~> [ TypeArgs ] ]
              [ KwImplements TypeList ]
              "{" { ClassMember } "}" ;

// The members: a constructor, methods and fields (tried in that order so 'constructor'
// and a method's '(' are recognized before the field form). A stray ';' is skipped.
// get/set accessors and generator/async methods are accepted but not implemented (they
// warn and contribute nothing to the class); an index signature is a type-layer member.
ClassMember = ClassSemi | IndexSig | Accessor | GenMethod | CtorDef | MethodDef | FieldDef ;
ClassSemi   <~~ push({skip: true}) ~~> = ";" ;
Accessor    <~~ notImpl("get/set accessor", up.pos); takeAll(); push({skip: true}) ~~>
            = MemberMods ( "get" KwEnd | "set" KwEnd ) Id ParamList [ TypeAnnot ] Block ;
GenMethod   <~~ notImpl("generator/async* method", up.pos); takeAll(); push({skip: true}) ~~>
            = MemberMods [ KwAsync ] "*" Id [ TypeParams ] ParamList [ TypeAnnot ] Block ;
// An index signature ([k: string]: T;) is pure type syntax; it emits nothing.
IndexSig    <~~ takeAll(); push({skip: true}) ~~>
            = MemberMods [ "readonly" KwEnd ] "[" Id ":" Type "]" TypeAnnot [ ";" ] ;

// A constructor. Its parameters may carry access modifiers (erased) and types (erased).
CtorDef     <~~ push(makeCtor(takeAll())) ~~>
            = { CtorMod } KwConstructor CtorParams Block ;
CtorMod     = ( "public" | "private" | "protected" ) KwEnd ;
CtorParams  <~~ push(takeAll()) ~~>
            = "(" [ CtorParam { "," CtorParam } ] ")" ;
CtorParam   = { PropMod } Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ "?" ] [ TypeAnnot ] ;
PropMod     = ( "public" | "private" | "protected" | "readonly" ) KwEnd ;

// A method (instance unless 'static'). Generics on the method, the parameter types and
// the return type are all erased; only the name, the parameter names and the body count.
MethodDef   <~~ push(makeMethod(takeAll())) ~~>
            = MemberMods Id <~~ push({mname: up.in}) ~~> [ TypeParams ] ParamList [ TypeAnnot ] Block ;

// A field (instance unless 'static'), with an optional '?'/'!' marker, an erased type
// annotation and an optional initializer.
FieldDef    <~~ push(makeField(takeAll())) ~~>
            = MemberMods Id <~~ push({fname: up.in}) ~~> [ "?" | "!" ] [ TypeAnnot ] [ "=" AssignExpr ] [ ";" ] ;

MemberMods  <~~ push({mods: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = { MemberMod <~~ push(up.in) ~~> } ;
MemberMod   = ( "public" | "private" | "protected" | "static" | "readonly" | "abstract" | "override" | "async" | "declare" ) KwEnd ;

// A balanced { ... } body consumed without interpreting it, so a construct can be
// ACCEPTED without being understood. Full string and template literals are matched
// first, so braces inside them are never miscounted.
SkipBlock   = "{" { SkipItem } "}" ;
SkipItem    = SkipDq | SkipSq | SkipTpl | SkipBlock | SkipOther ;
SkipDq      = '"' :whitespace() { SkipStrEsc | SkipDqChar } '"' :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
SkipSq      = "'" :whitespace() { SkipStrEsc | SkipSqChar } "'" :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
SkipTpl     = "`" :whitespace() { SkipTplSub | SkipStrEsc | SkipTplChar } "`" :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
SkipTplSub  = "${" :whitespace(Whitespace) { SkipItem } "}" ;
SkipStrEsc  = "\\" "\x00"..."\U0010ffff" ;
SkipDqChar  = "\x00"..."\x21" | "\x23"..."\x5b" | "\x5d"..."\U0010ffff" ;
SkipSqChar  = "\x00"..."\x26" | "\x28"..."\x5b" | "\x5d"..."\U0010ffff" ;
SkipTplChar = "\x00"..."\x5b" | "\x5d"..."\x5f" | "\x61"..."\U0010ffff" ;
SkipOther   = "\x00"..."\x21" | "\x23"..."\x26" | "\x28"..."\x5f" | "\x61"..."\x7a" | "\x7c" | "\x7e"..."\U0010ffff" ;

// --- TypeScript type expressions: parsed structurally and fully erased. ---
// NONE of these productions push onto the stack, so the value productions that embed a
// type annotation see exactly the stack they would without it. The grammar is scannerless
// but the global whitespace rule skips spaces after every terminal, so '< >', ':' and '|'
// behave as expected. A type is bounded by the surrounding syntax ('=', ';', ')', '=>',
// a function body '{'), so no explicit terminator token is needed.
TypeAnnot   = ":" Type ;
TypeList    = Type { "," Type } ;
Type        = FuncType | UnionType ;
FuncType    = [ TypeParams ] "(" [ FnTypeParam { "," FnTypeParam } ] ")" "=>" Type ;
FnTypeParam = [ "..." ] Id [ "?" ] [ TypeAnnot ] | Type ;
UnionType   = [ "|" ] IsectType { "|" IsectType } ;
IsectType   = [ "&" ] PostfixType { "&" PostfixType } ;
PostfixType = AtomType { ArraySfx } ;
ArraySfx    = "[" [ Type ] "]" ;
AtomType    = "(" Type ")" | ObjType | TupleType | LitType | NamedType ;
ObjType     = SkipBlock ;
TupleType   = "[" [ Type { "," Type } ] "]" ;
NamedType   = Id [ TypeArgs ] { "." Id [ TypeArgs ] } ;
TypeArgs    = "<" Type { "," Type } ">" ;
LitType     = StrTypeLit | NumTypeLit | "true" KwEnd | "false" KwEnd | "null" KwEnd | "undefined" KwEnd ;
StrTypeLit  = '"' :whitespace() { StrEsc | DqPlain } '"' :whitespace(Whitespace)
            | "'" :whitespace() { StrEsc | SqPlain } "'" :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
NumTypeLit  = ( "0" | "1"..."9" ) :whitespace() { "0"..."9" } [ "." "0"..."9" { "0"..."9" } ] :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
// A generic parameter declaration list: <T>, <K, V>, <T extends U>, <T = string>.
TypeParams  = "<" TypeParamDecl { "," TypeParamDecl } ">" ;
TypeParamDecl = Id [ KwExtends Type ] [ "=" Type ] ;

Null        <~~ push(makeConst(null)) ~~>      = "null" KwEnd ;
Undefined   <~~ push(makeConst(undefined)) ~~> = "undefined" KwEnd ;

VarRef      <~~ push(makeVarRef(up.in)) ~~>
            = Id ;

StringLit   = DqString | SqString ;
// The radix-prefixed literals (hex 0x, binary 0b, octal 0o) are tried before decimal,
// otherwise '0x1A' would stop after the '0'. A trailing bigint 'n' suffix is accepted
// and dropped (the value is a plain number).
NumberLit   = HexLit | BinLit | OctLit | DecLit ;

HexLit      <~~ push(makeConst(hexAt(up.in, 2, up.in.length - 2))) ~~>
            = ( "0x" | "0X" ) :whitespace() HexDigit { HexDigit } [ "n" ] :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
HexDigit    = "0"..."9" | "a"..."f" | "A"..."F" ;
BinLit      <~~ push(makeConst(radixVal(up.in, 2))) ~~>
            = ( "0b" | "0B" ) :whitespace() BinDigit { BinDigit } [ "n" ] :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
BinDigit    = "0"..."1" ;
OctLit      <~~ push(makeConst(radixVal(up.in, 8))) ~~>
            = ( "0o" | "0O" ) :whitespace() OctDigit { OctDigit } [ "n" ] :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
OctDigit    = "0"..."7" ;

// A regular-expression literal (/pattern/flags) is accepted at value position (division
// is a binary operator and never starts a primary). It is not implemented; the result
// value is undefined. The body matches a character class ([...] may contain '/'), an
// escape, or a plain character; a leading '/' or '*' is consumed by the comment layer,
// so a regex cannot begin with those (a rare limitation).
RegexLit    <~~ push(notImplExpr("regular expression literal", up.pos)) ~~>
            = "/" :whitespace() RegexPart { RegexPart } "/" { RegexFlag } :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
RegexPart   = RegexClass | RegexEsc | RegexChar ;
RegexClass  = "[" { RegexEsc | RegexClassChar } "]" ;
RegexEsc    = "\\" "\x00"..."\U0010ffff" ;
RegexChar   = "\x00"..."\x09" | "\x0b"..."\x0c" | "\x0e"..."\x2e" | "\x30"..."\x5a" | "\x5d"..."\U0010ffff" ;
RegexClassChar = "\x00"..."\x09" | "\x0b"..."\x0c" | "\x0e"..."\x5b" | "\x5e"..."\U0010ffff" ;
RegexFlag   = "a"..."z" ;

// The keywords end with a negative lookahead, so that e.g. 'iffy' or 'variable' stay identifiers.
KwVar       = ( "var" | "let" | "const" ) KwEnd ;
KwFunction  = "function" KwEnd ;
KwIf        = "if" KwEnd ;
KwElse      = "else" KwEnd ;
KwWhile     = "while" KwEnd ;
KwDo        = "do" KwEnd ;
KwFor       = "for" KwEnd ;
KwReturn    = "return" KwEnd ;
KwBreak     = "break" KwEnd ;
KwContinue  = "continue" KwEnd ;
KwThrow     = "throw" KwEnd ;
KwTypeof    = "typeof" KwEnd ;
KwSwitch    = "switch" KwEnd ;
KwCase      = "case" KwEnd ;
KwDefault   = "default" KwEnd ;
KwOf        = "of" KwEnd ;
KwIn        = "in" KwEnd ;
KwTry       = "try" KwEnd ;
KwCatch     = "catch" KwEnd ;
KwFinally   = "finally" KwEnd ;
KwClass     = "class" KwEnd ;
KwExtends   = "extends" KwEnd ;
KwImplements = "implements" KwEnd ;
KwNew       = "new" KwEnd ;
KwSuper     = "super" KwEnd ;
KwConstructor = "constructor" KwEnd ;
KwInterface = "interface" KwEnd ;
KwType      = "type" KwEnd ;
KwEnum      = "enum" KwEnd ;
KwAs        = "as" KwEnd ;
KwImport    = "import" KwEnd ;
KwExport    = "export" KwEnd ;
KwFrom      = "from" KwEnd ;
KwNamespace = "namespace" KwEnd ;
KwModule    = "module" KwEnd ;
KwGlobal    = "global" KwEnd ;
KwDeclare   = "declare" KwEnd ;
KwAsync     = "async" KwEnd ;
KwAwait     = "await" KwEnd ;
KwDelete    = "delete" KwEnd ;
KwVoid      = "void" KwEnd ;
KwYield     = "yield" KwEnd ;
KwInstanceof = "instanceof" KwEnd ;
KwDebugger  = "debugger" KwEnd ;

// A balanced ( ... ) span consumed without interpreting it (used by decorator arguments).
// String and template literals are matched first, so parens inside them are never counted.
SkipParen   = "(" { SkipDq | SkipSq | SkipTpl | SkipBlock | SkipParen | SkipPOther } ")" ;
SkipPOther  = "\x00"..."\x21" | "\x23"..."\x26" | "\x2a"..."\x5f" | "\x61"..."\x7a" | "\x7c" | "\x7e"..."\U0010ffff" ;

// ---


:startScript(~~

    // Shared interpreter machinery (scopes, BRK/CONT protocol, expression and
    // statement builders); language-specific behavior is configured on `core` below.
    include("lib/interp-core.js")

    // takeAll empties the local stack of the current tag and returns its items in push
    // order as a plain JS array. It only uses pop(), so it works independently of how
    // the runtime wraps the Go slice behind up.stack.
    // Resolves the JS string escapes (\n \t \r \0 \xNN \uNNNN, and \c for the char itself).
    // The host unescape() is for the grammar token syntax and rejects \' and \", so the
    // JS string literals bring their own unescaper.
    // ----- Scopes -----
    // 'scopes' is the active scope chain (innermost last). Every closure captures a copy
    // of the chain array; the scope objects inside stay shared, so later declarations in
    // an already captured scope are visible to the closure (that is what allows mutual
    // recursion between top level functions).

    // The host names that a JS program can use. Everything resolves to the goja
    // natives, so e.g. Math.imul or the string/array methods behave exactly like in JS.
    var hostGlobals = {
        "println": println, "print": print, "printf": printf, "sprintf": sprintf,
        "parseInt": parseInt, "parseFloat": parseFloat, "Math": Math, "String": String,
        "exit": exit
    }

    // Plain, unpinned scope entries: a variable holds its value directly and may
    // change type freely. No declare-before-use discipline.
    getVar = function(name) {
        for (var i = scopes.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            if (hasOwn(scopes[i], name)) return scopes[i][name]
        }
        if (hasOwn(hostGlobals, name)) return hostGlobals[name]
        fail("variable not defined: " + name)
    }
    declVar = function(name, value) {
        scopes[scopes.length - 1][name] = value
    }
    // Assignment walks the chain; a name that is nowhere declared becomes an
    // implicit global (real, non strict JavaScript), never an error.
    setVar = function(name, value) {
        for (var i = scopes.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            if (hasOwn(scopes[i], name)) { scopes[i][name] = value; return }
        }
        globalScope[name] = value
    }

    // ----- Statement signals -----
    // Statement thunks return undefined (fall through), BRK, CONT, or {isRet:true, v:...}.

    // ----- Functions -----
    // A MetaJS function value is a real (goja) JS function, so typeof, passing it around,
    // and calling it work natively. It closes over the scope chain of its creation.
    function makeClosure(params, bodyT, defScopes) {
        var env = defScopes.slice()
        return function() {
            var args = []
            for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) args.push(arguments[i])
            var saved = scopes
            scopes = env.slice()
            var sc = {}
            for (var j = 0; j < params.length; j++) {
                sc[params[j]] = args[j]
            }
            sc["arguments"] = args
            scopes.push(sc)
            var r = bodyT()
            scopes = saved
            return (r != undefined && r.isRet) ? r.v : undefined
        }
    }

    function getMember(o, k) {
        if (o == undefined) fail("member '" + k + "' of " + o) // Catches null and undefined.
        return o[k]
    }

    // ----- Expression thunks: function() -> value -----

    makeNeg = function(t) { return function() { return -t() } }
    function makeBitNot(t) { return function() { return ~t() } }
    function makeTypeof(t) { return function() { return typeof t() } }

    function makeArray(items) {
        return function() {
            var a = []
            for (var i = 0; i < items.length; i++) a.push(items[i]())
            return a
        }
    }
    // PropDef pops [valueThunk, key]; the key is an Id string, a constant string thunk
    // (StringLit), or a computed-key thunk ({[expr]: v}). It is kept as a thunk and
    // evaluated at run time - a computed key can read a variable, so it must not be
    // resolved at build time. Mirrors the compiler's makeProp (kt is the key thunk).
    function makeProp(valT, key) {
        return {kt: (typeof key == "string") ? makeConst(key) : key, t: valT}
    }
    // Objects carry a hidden __keys array recording their own keys in insertion order.
    // The tag dialect has no for-in and no Object.keys, and the -frozen engine cannot
    // enumerate a native object, so for-in reads this list instead. It matches the
    // compiler's js_keys (insertion order, __-prefixed keys never recorded).
    // A key that js_keys hides: the __-prefixed internal slots (__class, __keys, ...).
    function isInternalKey(key) {
        return typeof key == "string" && key.length >= 2 && key.charAt(0) == "_" && key.charAt(1) == "_"
    }
    function makeObject(props) {
        return function() {
            var o = {}
            var keys = []
            for (var i = 0; i < props.length; i++) {
                var k = props[i].kt()            // the key thunk (static or computed)
                o[k] = props[i].t()
                if (!isInternalKey(k)) {
                    var found = false
                    for (var j = 0; j < keys.length; j++) { if (keys[j] === k) { found = true } }
                    if (!found) keys.push(k)
                }
            }
            o["__keys"] = keys
            return o
        }
    }
    // Records a newly assigned key on a tracked object (an object carrying __keys). Plain
    // arrays and untracked values are left alone; only string, non-internal keys count.
    function trackKey(o, key) {
        if (o == undefined || o == null) { return }
        if (typeof key != "string") { return }
        if (isInternalKey(key)) { return }
        if (!hasOwn(o, "__keys")) { return }
        var ks = o["__keys"]
        for (var i = 0; i < ks.length; i++) { if (ks[i] === key) { return } }
        ks.push(key)
    }
    // The own keys of an object for for-in: a snapshot (so the body may add keys), the
    // __-prefixed internals never appear (they are never recorded in __keys).
    function jsKeys(o) {
        if (o == undefined || o == null) fail("for-in over " + o)
        if (hasOwn(o, "__keys")) return o["__keys"].slice()
        return []
    }

    function makeFunctionExpr(bodyT, params) {
        return function() { return makeClosure(params, bodyT, scopes) }
    }

    // Arrow function: items = [{aparams:[names]}, {body: stmtThunk} | {ebody: exprThunk}].
    // A block body is a statement thunk (returns undefined|signal, handled by
    // makeClosure); an expression body becomes an implicit 'return <expr>'.
    function makeArrow(items) {
        var params = items[0].aparams
        var bm = items[1]
        var bodyT = anytype // Either a block statement thunk or a synthesized return.
        if (bm.body != undefined) {
            bodyT = bm.body
        } else {
            var et = bm.ebody
            bodyT = function() { return {isRet: true, v: et()} }
        }
        return function() { return makeClosure(params, bodyT, scopes) }
    }

    // Template literal: items = [{str:"chunk"} | {expr: thunk}...] -> string thunk.
    // Starting from "" forces JS string coercion on every interpolated part.
    function makeTemplate(items) {
        return function() {
            var out = anytype // The running value is a string after the first "" seed.
            out = ""
            for (var i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
                if (items[i].str != undefined) { out = out + items[i].str }
                else { out = out + items[i].expr() }
            }
            return out
        }
    }

    // for-of / for-in. items = [name, "of"|"in", iterThunk, bodyThunk].
    // for-of genuinely iterates array elements / string characters by index.
    function makeForOf(items, pos) {
        var name = items[0]
        var iterT = items[2]
        var bodyT = items[3]
        if (items[1] == "in") {
            // for-in iterates the object's own keys (jsKeys), binding the loop variable
            // to each key string - mirrors the compiler's js_keys.
            return function() {
                var obj = anytype // The object whose keys are enumerated.
                obj = iterT()
                var ks = jsKeys(obj)
                scopes.push({})
                var res = undefined
                for (var i = 0; i < ks.length; i++) {
                    declVar(name, ks[i])
                    var r = bodyT()
                    if (r != undefined) {
                        if (r === BRK) break
                        if (r !== CONT) { res = r; break }
                    }
                }
                scopes.pop()
                return res
            }
        }
        return function() {
            var it = anytype // The iterable is an array or a string.
            it = iterT()
            scopes.push({}) // The loop header/variable get their own scope.
            var res = undefined
            for (var i = 0; i < it.length; i++) {
                declVar(name, it[i])
                var r = bodyT()
                if (r != undefined) {
                    if (r === BRK) break
                    if (r !== CONT) { res = r; break }
                }
            }
            scopes.pop()
            return res
        }
    }

    // A destructuring binding is not lowered; run the initializer (so its calls stay
    // visible) and bind nothing.
    function makeDestructure(init, pos) {
        notImpl("destructuring declaration", pos)
        return function() { init(); return undefined }
    }

    // try/catch/finally is not implemented; under -warn the try block runs.
    function makeTry(items, pos) { notImpl("try/catch/finally", pos); return items[0] }

    // ----- Classes (the __class machinery, mirrors typescript-to-llvm-ir.abnf) -----
    // An instance is a plain object carrying a __class descriptor; the descriptor holds
    // the methods (closures over the class-defining scope) and the __ctor. A method call
    // dispatches through mcall (below), which prepends the instance as the receiver and
    // follows __super for inheritance; super.m() invokes the parent's method on 'this'.

    // The class whose body is being built, captured by super() / super.m() at build time.
    var curClassName = ""

    // An instance method: a closure binding this = arguments[0], params from arguments[1..].
    function makeInstanceClosure(params, bodyT, defScopes) {
        var env = defScopes.slice()
        return function() {
            var self = arguments[0]
            var args = []
            for (var i = 1; i < arguments.length; i++) args.push(arguments[i])
            var saved = scopes
            scopes = env.slice()
            var sc = {}
            sc["this"] = self
            for (var j = 0; j < params.length; j++) sc[params[j]] = args[j]
            sc["arguments"] = args
            scopes.push(sc)
            var r = bodyT()
            scopes = saved
            return (r != undefined && r.isRet) ? r.v : undefined
        }
    }

    // A constructor closure: binds this = arguments[0], runs (for a default subclass ctor)
    // the implicit no-argument super, then the field initializers, then the body.
    function makeCtorClosure(params, bodyT, fields, defScopes, superName, isDefault) {
        var env = defScopes.slice()
        return function() {
            var self = arguments[0]
            var args = []
            for (var i = 1; i < arguments.length; i++) args.push(arguments[i])
            var saved = scopes
            scopes = env.slice()
            var sc = {}
            sc["this"] = self
            for (var j = 0; j < params.length; j++) sc[params[j]] = args[j]
            sc["arguments"] = args
            scopes.push(sc)
            if (isDefault && superName != null) {
                var supCls = getVar(superName)
                supCls.__ctor.apply(undefined, [self])
            }
            for (var k = 0; k < fields.length; k++) {
                var fv = (fields[k].init != null) ? fields[k].init() : undefined
                self[fields[k].name] = fv
                trackKey(self, fields[k].name)
            }
            if (bodyT != null) bodyT()
            scopes = saved
            return undefined
        }
    }

    // Method dispatch on an instance: follow the __class / __super chain. Native and
    // object-literal methods never reach here - foldCallMember calls this only when the
    // looked-up member was not itself a function value.
    function mcall(target, name, args) {
        if (target != undefined && target != null && target.__class != undefined) {
            var m = undefined
            for (var cl = target.__class; cl != undefined && m == undefined; cl = cl.__super) m = cl[name]
            if (typeof m != "function") fail("unknown method '" + name + "' on an instance")
            return m.apply(undefined, concat2impl([target], args))
        }
        fail("call of a non function value (method '" + name + "')")
    }

    function makeMethod(items) {
        var mods = items[0].mods
        var name = items[1].mname
        var params = items[2]   // The parameter names array (from ParamList).
        var body = items[3]
        var isStatic = false
        for (var i = 0; i < mods.length; i++) { if (mods[i] == "static") { isStatic = true } }
        return {kind: "method", name: name, statik: isStatic, params: params, body: body}
    }
    function makeCtor(items) {
        return {kind: "ctor", params: items[0], body: items[1]}
    }
    function makeField(items) {
        var mods = items[0].mods
        var name = items[1].fname
        var init = items.length > 2 ? items[2] : null
        var isStatic = false
        for (var i = 0; i < mods.length; i++) { if (mods[i] == "static") { isStatic = true } }
        return {kind: "field", name: name, statik: isStatic, init: init}
    }

    // A class declaration: build the descriptor object, attach static fields, the
    // constructor and the methods, then bind it in the current scope.
    function makeClassStmt(items) {
        var name = items[0].cname
        var superName = null
        var members = []
        for (var i = 1; i < items.length; i++) {
            if (items[i] == undefined) { continue }
            if (items[i].ext != undefined) { superName = items[i].ext }
            else if (items[i].skip != undefined) { continue }
            else { members.push(items[i]) }
        }
        var fields = []
        var methods = []
        var statics = []
        var ctorInfo = null
        for (var j = 0; j < members.length; j++) {
            var mm = members[j]
            if (mm.kind == "field") { if (mm.statik) { statics.push(mm) } else { fields.push(mm) } }
            else if (mm.kind == "method") { methods.push(mm) }
            else if (mm.kind == "ctor") { ctorInfo = mm }
        }
        return function() {
            var defScopes = scopes.slice()
            var cls = {}
            cls["__isclass"] = true
            cls["__name"] = name
            if (superName != null) {
                var sup = getVar(superName)
                if (sup == undefined || !sup.__isclass) fail("unknown superclass: " + superName)
                cls["__super"] = sup
            }
            for (var s = 0; s < statics.length; s++) {
                cls[statics[s].name] = (statics[s].init != null) ? statics[s].init() : undefined
            }
            if (ctorInfo != null) {
                cls["__ctor"] = makeCtorClosure(ctorInfo.params, ctorInfo.body, fields, defScopes, superName, false)
            } else {
                cls["__ctor"] = makeCtorClosure([], null, fields, defScopes, superName, true)
            }
            for (var mi = 0; mi < methods.length; mi++) {
                if (methods[mi].statik) { cls[methods[mi].name] = makeClosure(methods[mi].params, methods[mi].body, defScopes) }
                else { cls[methods[mi].name] = makeInstanceClosure(methods[mi].params, methods[mi].body, defScopes) }
            }
            declVar(name, cls)
            return undefined
        }
